{"id": "140186", "revid": "46586549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=140186", "title": "Lord Admiral", "text": "Lord Admiral is the official title of the ruler of &lt;a href=\"Kul%20Tiras%20%28kingdom%29\"&gt;Kul Tiras&lt;/a&gt;. The Lord Admiral commands the &lt;a href=\"Kul%20Tiran%20fleet\"&gt;Kul Tiran fleet&lt;/a&gt; and rules the nation in a similar fashion to a monarch. They are accompanied by the &lt;a href=\"Admiral%27s%20Elite%20Guard\"&gt;Admiral's Elite Guard&lt;/a&gt;. All known Lord Admirals have been from &lt;a href=\"House%20Proudmoore\"&gt;House Proudmoore&lt;/a&gt;.\nLady &lt;a href=\"Priscilla%20Ashvane\"&gt;Priscilla Ashvane&lt;/a&gt;, once Katherine Proudmoore's advisor and close friend, nearly acquired the position through an elaborate scheme to portray Katherine as being unable to protect the people of Kul Tiras. However, &lt;a href=\"Taelia%20Fordragon\"&gt;Taelia Fordragon&lt;/a&gt; and an &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;Alliance emissary&lt;/a&gt; thwarted Ashvane's plan by revealing the deception just moments after Katherine announced that she was stepping down.\nIn the RPG.\n&lt;a href=\"Tandred%20Proudmoore\"&gt;Tandred Proudmoore&lt;/a&gt; took the position of ruler of the Kul Tiras following his father's demise in &lt;a href=\"Theramore\"&gt;Theramore&lt;/a&gt;."}
