{"id": "19289", "revid": "49848256", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19289", "title": "Lord Arkkoroc", "text": "Lord Arkkoroc is a &lt;a href=\"sea%20giant\"&gt;sea giant&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"quest%20giver\"&gt;quest giver&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Arkkoran\"&gt;Temple of Arkkoran&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Azshara%20%28Classic%29\"&gt;Azshara&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Loramus%20Thalipedes\"&gt;Loramus Thalipedes&lt;/a&gt; described him as a lesser deity, and his sons patrolled around the temple. Many of Lord Arkkoroc's sons were slain by the &lt;a href=\"hydra\"&gt;hydra&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Hetaera\"&gt;Hetaera&lt;/a&gt;, and he now seeks revenge.\nFollowing the &lt;a href=\"Cataclysm%20%28event%29\"&gt;Cataclysm&lt;/a&gt;, Arkkoroc has vanished and presumably was slain. The &lt;a href=\"naga\"&gt;naga&lt;/a&gt; are using a gem called the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20Arkkoroc\"&gt;Heart of Arkkoroc&lt;/a&gt; to control his sons.\nIn the RPG.\nAlso known as Arkkoran, he is the supposed god of the &lt;a href=\"sea%20giant\"&gt;sea giant&lt;/a&gt;s. The &lt;a href=\"makrura\"&gt;makrura&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"murloc\"&gt;murloc&lt;/a&gt;s in the area consider him some kind of divinity as well. Arkkoran only leaves the temple when he is in a foul mood. The religion surrounding him is also called Arkkoroc."}
{"id": "19798", "revid": "41522423", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19798", "title": "Lord Arthas", "text": ""}
{"id": "556993", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=556993", "title": "Lord Arthur Waycrest", "text": "Lord Arthur Waycrest was the patriarch and Lord of &lt;a href=\"House%20Waycrest\"&gt;House Waycrest&lt;/a&gt;. \nHistory.\nAs a descendant of &lt;a href=\"Arom%20Waycrest\"&gt;Arom Waycrest&lt;/a&gt;, Arthur would eventually take his position as Lord of House Waycrest. He would fall in love and marry a woman named &lt;a href=\"Meredith%20Waycrest\"&gt;Meredith&lt;/a&gt; and from their marriage, they conceived one daughter, &lt;a href=\"Lucille%20Waycrest\"&gt;Lucille Waycrest&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter Lucille grew up, she fell in love with &lt;a href=\"Alexander%20Treadward\"&gt;Alexander Treadward&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"merchant\"&gt;merchant&lt;/a&gt;. Arthur was pleased that she was happy and apparently approved of the young man, and after the couple became engaged, looked forward to officiating their wedding as Lord of &lt;a href=\"Drustvar\"&gt;Drustvar&lt;/a&gt;, writing out a speech he planned to give for the occasion. Meredith disapproved of the marriage as Alexander was a \"common merchant.\" She tried to convince her husband to call it off even on the wedding day, but he compared the young couple to their own relationship, as Lucille was following her heart, just as Arthur had. Having failed to sway Arthur to her line of thinking, unbeknownst to him on the day of the wedding Meredith hired &lt;a href=\"Roland%20the%20Knife\"&gt;Roland the Knife&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Hand\"&gt;Red Hand&lt;/a&gt; to assassinate Alexander. With him dead on the ground, Arthur stayed with his shocked and grieving daughter to protect her.\nAll was fine in his land until rumours started going around that he fell to a deadly illness and that Meredith would refuse to leave his side. Stricken with grief due to her ailing husband, Lady Waycrest called out to any power that could save him. &lt;a href=\"Gorak%20Tul\"&gt;Gorak Tul&lt;/a&gt; answered her cry and promised that \u2014 for a price \u2014 death would never part the couple. She started the &lt;a href=\"Heartsbane%20Coven\"&gt;Heartsbane Coven&lt;/a&gt;, but Arthur fell out of sight. His last whereabouts were heard from &lt;a href=\"Marshal%20Everit%20Reade\"&gt;Marshal Everit Reade&lt;/a&gt; who told Lucille that her father had been captured.\nWhen the newly formed &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20Embers\"&gt;Order of Embers&lt;/a&gt; charged from &lt;a href=\"Upper%20Corlain\"&gt;Upper Corlain&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Waycrest%20Manor\"&gt;Waycrest Manor&lt;/a&gt;. They found a mutated, undead Arthur standing next to his wife, and Meredith, telling their daughter that he was \"alive and well\", revealed she intended on Arthur becoming Lord of all Kul Tiras.\nAs the Order of Embers went deeper into the manor, they entered the &lt;a href=\"Catacombs%20%28Waycrest%20Manor%29\"&gt;Catacombs&lt;/a&gt; and found Arthur next to his wife. Just as they lived, they died together in their final confrontation with Meredith refusing to let him go.\nQuotes.\nOh, hello there. I'm afraid we haven't met, but thank you for being here for my dear Lucy.\nHow can I help you?\nWell, this is a little embarrassing.\nYou see, I had my speech written out in my notebook, but I seem to have... Misplaced it.\nIt must be somewhere in this room. If you could help me find it, I would be eternally grateful!"}
{"id": "311146", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=311146", "title": "Lord Ashbury the 1st", "text": "Lord Ashbury the 1st was a &lt;a href=\"Gilneas%20%28kingdom%29\"&gt;Gilnean&lt;/a&gt; noble and the father of &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Ashbury\"&gt;Baron Ashbury&lt;/a&gt;. Lord Ashbury helped King &lt;a href=\"Archibald%20Greymane\"&gt;Archibald Greymane&lt;/a&gt; build Gilneas up to a nation of great power. King Archibald always told his son &lt;a href=\"Genn%20Greymane\"&gt;Prince Genn&lt;/a&gt; to trust in the Ashburys\u2019 fidelity to the crown because of the accomplishments of Lord Ashbury."}
{"id": "460155", "revid": "42014766", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=460155", "title": "Val'zuun", "text": "Val'zuun is a &lt;a href=\"eredar\"&gt;man'ari eredar&lt;/a&gt; informant of unknown origin found sitting in an alcove of &lt;a href=\"the%20Underbelly%20Descent\"&gt;the Underbelly Descent&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Dalaran\"&gt;Dalaran&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe is one of the &lt;a href=\"The%20Uncrowned\"&gt;Uncrowned&lt;/a&gt; contacts that &lt;a href=\"Rogue%23Subtlety\"&gt;subtlety&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"rogue\"&gt;rogue&lt;/a&gt;s in search of the &lt;a href=\"Fangs%20of%20the%20Devourer\"&gt;Fangs of the Devourer&lt;/a&gt; speak to in order to learn the whereabouts of the eredar assassin &lt;a href=\"Akaari%20Shadowgore\"&gt;Akaari Shadowgore&lt;/a&gt;, who wields the Fangs. Val'zuun tells the rogue that Akaari is already present in Dalaran, spying for her masters, but says that he won't reveal her exact location until the rogue brings him a &lt;a href=\"Rune%20of%20Portals\"&gt;rune of portals&lt;/a&gt;. After &lt;a href=\"Valeera%20Sanguinar\"&gt;Valeera Sanguinar&lt;/a&gt; and the subtlety rogue \"borrow\" the rune from &lt;a href=\"Archmage%20Celindra\"&gt;Archmage Celindra&lt;/a&gt;, Val'zuun informs them that Akaari is at the &lt;a href=\"Legerdemain%20Lounge\"&gt;Legerdemain Lounge&lt;/a&gt;. However, once the rogue confronts and defeats Akaari, it is revealed to be a ruse: Akaari's body transforms into that of a &lt;a href=\"Shadowgore%20Bloodmaiden\"&gt;Shadowgore Bloodmaiden&lt;/a&gt; upon death.\nValeera confronts Val'zuun, but he claims that he did not know about the plot and says that he can open a portal to Akaari's stronghold using the rune of portals he was provided earlier. Keeping his promise, Val'zuun creates a &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Gateway\"&gt;Twisted Gateway&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Shadowgore%20Citadel\"&gt;Shadowgore Citadel&lt;/a&gt; and guides the subtlety rogue through the fortress from afar, allowing the rogue to confront the real Akaari, kill her and claim the Fangs of the Devourer. When the rogue returns, Val'zuun congratulates them on their victory and tells them that Valeera is awaiting their return, before he walks off into the &lt;a href=\"Underbelly\"&gt;Underbelly&lt;/a&gt; and disappears.\nQuests.\nHe needs to be spoken to during &lt;a href=\"The%20Shadows%20Reveal\"&gt;The Shadows Reveal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"A%20Matter%20of%20Finesse\"&gt;A Matter of Finesse&lt;/a&gt;."}
