{"id": "50422", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50422", "title": "Valdred Moray", "text": "&lt;tabber&gt;\nRetail=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;\nValdred Moray is a &lt;a href=\"Forsaken\"&gt;Forsaken&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Deathknell%20Graves\"&gt;Deathknell Graves&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Tirisfal%20Glades\"&gt;Tirisfal Glades&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nValdred Moray was once good friends with &lt;a href=\"Raleigh%20Andrean\"&gt;Raleigh Andrean&lt;/a&gt; and his wife &lt;a href=\"Deliah\"&gt;Deliah&lt;/a&gt;. However, after &lt;a href=\"Scourge\"&gt;Scourge&lt;/a&gt; came to &lt;a href=\"Lordaeron\"&gt;Lordaeron&lt;/a&gt; Raleigh was killed and then brought back as a member of the &lt;a href=\"Forsaken\"&gt;Forsaken&lt;/a&gt;. During this time, Valdred murdered Deliah. \nAfter killing his former friend, Valdred fled to the &lt;a href=\"Greymane%20Wall\"&gt;Greymane Wall&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Silverpine%20Forest\"&gt;Silverpine Forest&lt;/a&gt; where he wanted to enter &lt;a href=\"Gilneas%20peninsula\"&gt;Gilneas&lt;/a&gt;. However, the gates of the &lt;a href=\"Greymane%20Wall\"&gt;Greymane Wall&lt;/a&gt; remained shut. He stubbornly stood outside, waiting for it to open until an orc cut off &lt;a href=\"Valdred%27s%20Hands\"&gt;his hands&lt;/a&gt; and left him to die.\nHis corpse was later transported to the graveyard in &lt;a href=\"Deathknell\"&gt;Deathknell&lt;/a&gt; located within the &lt;a href=\"Tirisfal%20Glades\"&gt;Tirisfal Glades&lt;/a&gt;. He was then raised in undeath by the &lt;a href=\"Val%27kyr\"&gt;Val'kyr&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Aradne\"&gt;Aradne&lt;/a&gt;. Valdred had trouble coping with his newly undead status and became further distressed when he realized his hands were not his own. After being informed that &lt;a href=\"Undertaker%20Mordo\"&gt;Undertaker Mordo&lt;/a&gt; sewed new hands on him, Valdred relaxed, reflecting upon how he never thought he'd be fighting for the Forsaken. He then wondered what to do next, and was informed by the player to seek out Undertaker Mordo."}
