{"id": "193309", "revid": "40389549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=193309", "title": "Valduran the Stormborn (quest)", "text": "Objectives.\nUse Bouldercrag's War Horn when you have found Valduran the Stormborn. Defeat Valduran the Stormborn and return to &lt;a href=\"Bouldercrag%20the%20Rockshaper\"&gt;Bouldercrag the Rockshaper&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Bouldercrag%27s%20Refuge\"&gt;Bouldercrag's Refuge&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nWe have no choice, &lt;name&gt;. What you learned in &lt;a href=\"Mimir%27s%20Workshop\"&gt;Mimir's Workshop&lt;/a&gt; means that we must act before Valduran can complete and unleash his new weapon.\nEven now, the refuge's defenders fight to buy us time to deal with Valduran the Stormborn.\nYou must go to &lt;a href=\"Nidavelir\"&gt;Nidavelir&lt;/a&gt;, across the &lt;a href=\"Snowdrift%20Plains\"&gt;Snowdrift Plains&lt;/a&gt; to the southwest, and then find and face Valduran. But you will not be alone. Bring this war horn with you and sound it as you prepare to face the leader of our enemies. &lt;a href=\"Bruor%20Ironbane\"&gt;Bruor&lt;/a&gt; and I will aid you in this battle. \nProgress.\nValduran must be dealt with before the refuge falls.\nCompletion.\nAt last, Valduran is dead, and the stormforged are weakened, but if his boasting is true, we must continue fighting the stormforged in his absence. This weapon they're building could be the end of us.\nNotes.\nValduran is at , the last building in &lt;a href=\"Nidavelir\"&gt;Nidavelir&lt;/a&gt;.\nUse the war horn to summon Bouldercrag and Bruor to start the fight.\nLet the elites tank Valduran. Valduran will likely open with \"Ball Lightning\" on the player, which inflicts 850 Nature damage every second to enemies who enter the area. He also casts Lightning Bolt on his main aggro target for ~2000 Nature damage and \"Spark Frenzy\", where Sparks fly from the caster in all directions, doing 329 to 381 Nature damage per spark.\nVictory\nIt is possible to fail this quest if you do not participate in the fight. Not generating enough aggro could be the source of the problem, however GM's have not commented on its mechanics. As a healer, you may have trouble successfully completing it on your first attempt. The allies that you spawn do not require healing, so feel free to attack as much as you can."}
