{"id": "194153", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=194153", "title": "Alliance Assembly", "text": "The Alliance Assembly (aka the Assembly of Theramore or just the Assembly) is the ruling council of &lt;a href=\"Theramore\"&gt;Theramore&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Kalimdor\"&gt;Kalimdor&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Human\"&gt;Human&lt;/a&gt;s hold five seats in the council while &lt;a href=\"High%20elf\"&gt;high elves&lt;/a&gt; hold two and &lt;a href=\"Ironforge%20dwarf\"&gt;Ironforge dwarves&lt;/a&gt; none. The meetings of the members reveal a considerable strain among the city's residents given the racial distrust and underepresentation in the council. Its chambers are located in the &lt;a href=\"Foothold%20Citadel\"&gt;Foothold Citadel&lt;/a&gt;. Meetings between the &lt;a href=\"night%20elf\"&gt;night elf&lt;/a&gt; ambassadors and the Assembly sometimes ended in sharp words because of the conflict between the Kaldorei and Quel'dorei.\nThe Assembly wanted intelligence about a &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; encampment and the &lt;a href=\"tinker\"&gt;tinker&lt;/a&gt;s agreed to do it. &lt;a href=\"Sunstorm\"&gt;Sunstorm&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Nuji%20Kodosbreath\"&gt;Nuji Kodosbreath&lt;/a&gt; went to investigate, leading &lt;a href=\"steamwarrior\"&gt;steamwarrior&lt;/a&gt;s there. Previously, the Assembly wasn't satisfied when Sunstorm's men killed Horde members in a last raid.\nThe &lt;a href=\"noble%27s%20swordsmen\"&gt;noble's swordsmen&lt;/a&gt; is a roomsized apparatus commissioned from a group of tinkers by advisors to the Alliance Assembly; they wished to settle disputes with traditional swordfights, yet didn't want to risk any true physical harm.\nA brilliant Alliance &lt;a href=\"engineer\"&gt;engineer&lt;/a&gt; invented &lt;a href=\"substitution%20engine\"&gt;substitution engine&lt;/a&gt;s recently; they remain one of the Alliance Assembly's greatest secrets."}
