{"id": "152087", "revid": "3154973", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=152087", "title": "Aredek", "text": "Aredek, affectionately known as \"Decky\" or \"Ducky\", is a &lt;a href=\"Blizz\"&gt;Blizz&lt;/a&gt;ard employee who frequently used to post on the US World of Warcraft &lt;a href=\"http%3A//forums.worldofwarcraft.com/board.html%3Fsid%3D1%26amp%3BforumId%3D11112\"&gt;Customer Service Forum&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe was introduced in early 2008 and replaced &lt;a href=\"Auryk\"&gt;Auryk&lt;/a&gt; on the nightshift. He eventually moved to the morning shift (7am \u2013 4pm CDT), which he held for the remainder of his tenure as a Customer Service Forum representative, and &lt;a href=\"Orlyia\"&gt;Orlyia&lt;/a&gt; took over the night shift when she joined the team.\n&lt;a href=\"Belfaire\"&gt;Belfaire&lt;/a&gt; often seemed jealous and intimidated by Aredek's purported \"impressive facial hair\".\nOn July 28th, 2010, Aredek resigned his position as a CS Forum representative. In his farewell thread, he announced that he would be moving to the Irvine, CA office to join former colleagues &lt;a href=\"Syndri\"&gt;Syndri&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Malkorix\"&gt;Malkorix&lt;/a&gt; as they pursue new opportunities within the company. \nHe has an NPC named after him (&lt;a href=\"Brandon%20Eiredeck\"&gt;Brandon Eiredeck&lt;/a&gt;) in the &lt;a href=\"Culling%20of%20Stratholme%20%28instance%29\"&gt;Culling of Stratholme&lt;/a&gt; instance."}
{"id": "372494", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=372494", "title": "Aredhel", "text": "Aredhel was the wife of &lt;a href=\"Karlain\"&gt;Karlain&lt;/a&gt; who was accidentally killed by her husband when a man seeking to be Karlain's apprentice attempted to rape her. An image of her appeared before Karlain in &lt;a href=\"Karazhan\"&gt;Karazhan&lt;/a&gt; years later due to the tower's mysterious ability to grant visions of the past and future but since Karazhan is cursed with fel magic, its visions distort the truth for malicious intent. At first, Karlain and &lt;a href=\"Mardigan\"&gt;Mardigan&lt;/a&gt; witnessed a false vision in which young Karlain did not have time for Aredhel and she found herself in the company of a young novice. Karlain returned home and caught her sleeping with the man. He killed them both in a rage and the vision ended. Mardigan was angered by the vision and lost himself to his beastial fury but &lt;a href=\"Revil%20Kost\"&gt;Revil Kost&lt;/a&gt; placed the cloak of purity on him which warded off the tower's fel magic, allowing Mardigan to see the true vision in which Aredhel died accidentally when Karlain used a spell that vanquished her attempted rapist but accidentally also brought down debris upon her, crushing her and killing her."}
