{"id": "554301", "revid": "40286693", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=554301", "title": "Argent Dawn embassy", "text": "The Argent Dawn embassy is an unnamed building in the &lt;a href=\"Craftsmen%27s%20Terrace\"&gt;Craftsmen's Terrace&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Night%20elf\"&gt;night elven&lt;/a&gt; capital of &lt;a href=\"Darnassus\"&gt;Darnassus&lt;/a&gt;. The embassy is maintained by the &lt;a href=\"Argent%20Dawn\"&gt;Argent Dawn&lt;/a&gt;, a holy order dedicated to combating evil forces. The building's first floor serves as an &lt;a href=\"alchemy\"&gt;alchemy&lt;/a&gt; shop, while the second floor hosts the embassy proper. &lt;a href=\"Feero%27s%20Holy%20Hammer\"&gt;Feero's Holy Hammer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"The%20Purifier%27s%20Prayer%20Book\"&gt;The Purifier's Prayer Book&lt;/a&gt; would notably be delivered to the embassy after being retrieved from the bodies of their owners, &lt;a href=\"Feero%20Ironhand\"&gt;Feero Ironhand&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Delgren%20the%20Purifier\"&gt;Delgren the Purifier&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn the RPG.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Argent%20Dawn\"&gt;Argent Dawn&lt;/a&gt; seeks to liberate locations that have been taken by evil forces. Because of that, they move from place to place, but by necessity they have a few stable headquarters, both on major cities such as &lt;a href=\"Darnassus\"&gt;Darnassus&lt;/a&gt; and at more humble locations, such as &lt;a href=\"Chillwind%20Camp\"&gt;Chillwind Camp&lt;/a&gt;. While the Argent Dawn is a neutral organization, some of its founding members were once &lt;a href=\"Knights%20of%20the%20Silver%20Hand\"&gt;Knights of the Silver Hand&lt;/a&gt;, as such they still hold some level of influence within the &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt;, who honors them with their own headquarters in Darnassus, and a few buildings in other cities."}
{"id": "17052", "revid": "40581559", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17052", "title": "Argent Dawn mantles", "text": "When you are with the &lt;a href=\"Argent%20Dawn\"&gt;Argent Dawn&lt;/a&gt;, you will be able to purchase Mantles, which give a magic resistance enchant on your shoulder armor. \nBe sure to note that to be able to purchase the Arcane/Shadow/Fire/Frost/Nature Mantles, you must turn in 10 &lt;a href=\"Argent%20Dawn%20Valor%20Token\"&gt;Argent Dawn Valor Token&lt;/a&gt;s. This is only required once. At this point, you can purchase these Mantles from any Argent Dawn vendor.\nThe Chromatic Mantle is only available at and requires turning in an additional 25 &lt;a href=\"Argent%20Dawn%20Valor%20Token\"&gt;Argent Dawn Valor Token&lt;/a&gt;s.\nBefore the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Crusade\"&gt;Burning Crusade&lt;/a&gt; expansion, shoulder enchants are only available from here, from rewards for with &lt;a href=\"Zandalar%20Tribe\"&gt;Zandalar Tribe&lt;/a&gt;, and as drops from the frost dragon &lt;a href=\"Sapphiron\"&gt;Sapphiron&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Naxxramas\"&gt;Naxxramas&lt;/a&gt;."}
