{"id": "214278", "revid": "40389549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=214278", "title": "Argent Squire", "text": "The Argent Squire is acquired when you become a &lt;a href=\"Champion\"&gt;Champion&lt;/a&gt; of your &lt;a href=\"race\"&gt;race&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Argent%20Tournament\"&gt;Argent Tournament&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis item summons an Argent Squire which can carry the &lt;a href=\"banner\"&gt;banner&lt;/a&gt; for any &lt;a href=\"faction\"&gt;faction&lt;/a&gt; that the player has earned the right to Champion. When becoming champion of all races, you will be able to buy a &lt;a href=\"Argent%20Pony%20Bridle\"&gt;mini horse&lt;/a&gt; for the squire, which will reward you with an achievement, and which will enable your squire to go to the shop, mailbox, or the bank for you for 3 minutes, with a 4 hour cooldown. \nThis is handy for when you're in a dungeon and need materials for spells, or if you forgot that quest item in the bank. Remember when he returns he needs 4 hours of rest before he can go shopping again. \nAlthough this is summonable on other &lt;a href=\"character\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt;s, only the character with which you have purchased the &lt;a href=\"Argent%20Pony%20Bridle\"&gt;Argent Pony Bridle&lt;/a&gt; is able to use the vendor, mailbox and bank services.\nThe design for the squire, including an overstuffed backpack and a banner, may be an homage to the squires in the popular movie \"\".\nPet Journal.\n\"Many of &lt;a href=\"Stormwind\"&gt;Stormwind&lt;/a&gt;'s youth joined the &lt;a href=\"Argent%20Crusade\"&gt;Argent Crusade&lt;/a&gt; as squires, hoping to one day serve the Holy Light in battle.\""}
{"id": "183725", "revid": "46586549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=183725", "title": "Argent Stand", "text": "The Argent Stand is the main base of the &lt;a href=\"Argent%20Crusade\"&gt;Argent Crusade&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Zul%27Drak\"&gt;Zul'Drak&lt;/a&gt;, and was built in a &lt;a href=\"Drakkari\"&gt;Drakkari&lt;/a&gt; structure which once might have been some sort of open air market. The central area of the Argent Stand functions as an &lt;a href=\"inn\"&gt;inn&lt;/a&gt; and provides &lt;a href=\"rest\"&gt;rest&lt;/a&gt;.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"war%20against%20the%20Lich%20King\"&gt;war against the Lich King&lt;/a&gt;, it was initially chosen by the Argent Crusade as a defensive position to keep the &lt;a href=\"Scourge\"&gt;Scourge&lt;/a&gt; from taking the second tier of Zul'Drak. However, that effort failed, but the crusade hasn't given up.\nFollowing the &lt;a href=\"war%20against%20the%20Jailer\"&gt;war against the Jailer&lt;/a&gt;, the brothers &lt;a href=\"Bronzebeard\"&gt;Bronzebeard&lt;/a&gt; reported that this heavily fortified area still hosts quite the population of crusaders fighting the Scourge. They described it as a safe enough place, where they were able to sleep, though surrounded by the sounds of battle as the undead threw themselves against the fortifications."}
{"id": "196800", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=196800", "title": "Argent Tome", "text": "Argent Tome is a rare quality trinket bought from an &lt;a href=\"Argent%20Quartermaster\"&gt;Argent Quartermaster&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Scourge%20Invasion\"&gt;Scourge Invasion&lt;/a&gt; pre-WotLK event for . It will summon an untargetable tome several yards in front of you which will cast Argent Wisdom once, doing ~250-350 Holy damage to everything around it."}
